{"sha": "f743fe231663e32d52db987650d0ec3381a777af", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0MTM2NTMxMDA6Zjc0M2ZlMjMxNjYzZTMyZDUyZGI5ODc2NTBkMGVjMzM4MWE3NzdhZg==", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Julian Brown", "email": "julian@codesourcery.com", "date": "2021-01-30T01:18:07Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Julian Brown", "email": "julian@codesourcery.com", "date": "2021-02-04T23:05:50Z"}, "message": "openacc: Use class_pointer instead of pointer attribute for class types\n\nElsewhere in the Fortran front-end, the class_pointer attribute is\nused for BT_CLASS entities instead of the pointer attribute. This patch\nfollows suit for OpenACC. I couldn't actually come up with a test case\nwhere this makes a difference (i.e., where \"class_pointer\" and \"pointer\"\nhave different values at this point in the code), but this may nonetheless\nfix a latent bug.\n\ngcc/fortran/\n\t* trans-openmp.c (gfc_trans_omp_clauses): Use class_pointer attribute\n\tfor BT_CLASS.", "tree": {"sha": "e4f3bc1833f3baf1cddedd8a96eded74f06b8404", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/trees/e4f3bc1833f3baf1cddedd8a96eded74f06b8404"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/commits/f743fe231663e32d52db987650d0ec3381a777af", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/f743fe231663e32d52db987650d0ec3381a777af", "html_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commit/f743fe231663e32d52db987650d0ec3381a777af", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/f743fe231663e32d52db987650d0ec3381a777af/comments", "author": {"login": "jtb20", "id": 6094880, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjYwOTQ4ODA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6094880?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jtb20", "html_url": "https://github.com/jtb20", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jtb20/followers", "following_url": "https: